      "set:html": '<ol>\n<li>\n<p>In Builder’s visual editor, create a new content entry with the following values:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>title:</strong> ‘First post, woohoo!‘</li>\n<li><strong>slug:</strong> ‘first-post-woohoo’</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Complete your post using the <strong>Add Block</strong> button and add a text field with some post content.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In the text field above the editor, give your entry a name. This is how it will be listed in the Builder app.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>When you’re ready click the <strong>Publish</strong> button in the upper right corner.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Create as many posts as you like, ensuring that all content entries contain a <code dir="auto">title</code> and a <code dir="auto">slug</code> as well as some post content.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>'
